'''Tim Robinson''' (born May 23, 1981) is an American actor, comedian, and writer best known for starring in the [[Comedy Central]] series [[Detroiters (TV series)|''Detroiters'']].<ref>{{cite web|title=30 Under 30: Comedians to Watch |url=http://www.splashlife.com/article/30-under-30-comedians-watch?page=3 |work=Tim Robinson |publisher=spashlife |accessdate=September 14, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130620064335/http://www.splashlife.com/article/30-under-30-comedians-watch?page=3 |archivedate=June 20, 2013 }}</ref><ref name=NBCbio>{{cite web|title=Cast Bios |url=http://www.nbc.com/saturday-night-live/bios/tim-robinson_38.shtml |work=Tim Robinson |publisher=NBC |accessdate=September 14, 2012 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120914012350/http://www.nbc.com/saturday-night-live/bios/tim-robinson_38.shtml |archivedate=September 14, 2012 }}</ref> Prior to that, he was known for his work as a writer and cast member on ''[[Saturday Night Live]]''.
==Life and career== {{Expand section|date=September 2012}} Robinson is a native of [[Detroit]], [[Michigan]].<ref name=NBCbio/> He has performed at [[The Second City]], [[iO Theater]], and [[Just for Laughs]].<ref name=NBCbio/><ref>{{cite news|last=L. McCarthy|first=Sean|title=From Second City to SNL: Aidy Bryant, Tim Robinson set to join cast of Saturday Night Live|url=http://thecomicscomic.com/2012/09/07/from-second-city-to-snl-aidy-bryant-tim-robinson-eyed-for-new-cast-roles-at-saturday-night-live/|newspaper=The Comic's Comic|date=September 7, 2012}}</ref> He filmed a 2011 television pilot for [[Comedy Central]] called ''My Mans'', but the show was not picked up by the network.<ref>{{cite news|last=Thomas|first=Mike|title=‘SNL’ hires three new actors, all trained in Chicago|url=http://www.suntimes.com/entertainment/television/15063557-421/snl-hires-three-new-actors-all-trained-in-chicago.html|newspaper=Chicago Sun-Times|date=September 10, 2012|archiveurl=http://hollywood-news-now.blogspot.com/2012/09/snl-hires-three-new-actors-all-trained.html|archivedate=October 22, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Goldberg|first=Lesley|title=NBC Near Deals for Two New 'Saturday Night Live' Cast Members|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/saturday-night-live-cast-aidy-bryant-tim-robinson-season-38-368820|newspaper=The Hollywood Reporter|date=September 7, 2012}}</ref> Robinson is a 2000 graduate of [[Clarkston High School (Michigan)|Clarkston High School]] in [[Clarkston, Michigan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.freep.com/article/20120910/ENT03/120910067/tim-robinson-saturday-night-live |title=Michigan native joins 'Saturday Night Live' cast in Saturday season-opener &#124; TV and Radio &#124; Detroit Free Press |publisher=freep.com |date=2012-09-10 |accessdate=2012-09-27}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=CHRIS LAINEOf The Oakland Press |url=http://www.sourcenewspapers.com/articles/2012/09/13/news/doc50524cd982892972231296.txt |title=Clarkston grad Tim Robinson newest addition to 38th season of 'Saturday Night Live' - News |publisher=Source Newspapers |date=2012-09-13 |accessdate=2012-09-27}}</ref> Robinson and his wife Heather have two children, a daughter and a son.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.secondcity.com/history/alumni/detail/1151/ |title=History - Alumni - - The Second City - 50 Years of Funny |publisher=The Second City |date= |accessdate=2012-09-27}}</ref>
On September 15, 2012, Robinson made his debut as a featured player on ''Saturday Night Live''.<ref>{{cite news|last=Levin|first=Gary|title='Saturday Night Live' adds three new cast members|url=http://content.usatoday.com/communities/entertainment/post/2012/09/Saturday-Night-Live-adds-three-new-cast-members-70000041/snl-adds-three-new-cast-members/70000041/1#.UFEhelGByS0|newspaper=USA Today|date=September 10, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=‘Saturday Night Live’ adds 3 performers for upcoming season after departures of Wiig, Samberg|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/entertainment/tv/saturday-night-live-adds-3-performers-for-upcoming-season-after-departures-of-wiig-samberg/2012/09/10/e1bc7170-fb5f-11e1-98c6-ec0a0a93f8eb_story.html|newspaper=The Washington Post (The Associated Press)|date=September 10, 2012}}</ref> Prior to joining the cast of ''SNL'', Robinson was cast as a series regular in the unaired [[CBS]] sitcom ''[[Friend Me]]''. On September 15, 2013, it was announced that Robinson would work on the writing staff rather than continue being a cast member, making Tim Robinson the second cast member after [[Brian Doyle-Murray]] to go from featured player to staff writer, and the first ''SNL'' performer to become a writer after being cast only as a featured player. As a cast member, his celebrity impressions included [[Ben Bailey]] and [[Bill Cowher]]. Robinson also acted as the reoccurring character Carl, an elderly retail worker who would always get insulted by Niff ([[Bobby Moynihan]]) and Dana ([[Cecily Strong]]).
Robinson has appeared twice on late-night NBC talk show ''[[Late Night with Seth Meyers]]'' as Dale, who acts as host [[Seth Meyers]]' "emergency sidekick." Robinson's first appearance was on the February 28, 2014 episode, during the "Next Week's News" sketch, and his second appearance was on the April 8, 2014 episode, during the "Celebrity Drunk Texts" sketch.
In 2016, he wrote and starred in his own 30-minute episode of the [[sketch show]] ''[[Netflix Presents: The Characters]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/netflix-orders-innovative-sketch-series-861049|title=Netflix Orders Innovative Sketch Series 'The Characters' (Exclusive)|publisher=The Hollywood Reporter|date=February 1, 2016|accessdate=February 2, 2016}}</ref>
Robinson is also the co-creator and co-star of [[Detroiters (TV series)|''Detroiters'']], along with fellow Detroit native [[Sam Richardson (actor)|Sam Richardson]]. The show premiered on [[Comedy Central]] on February 7, 2017.
In April 2017, Robinson guest starred on Fox's [[Making History (TV series)|Making History]] as [[Al Capone]].
